richTextLabel.label: No more tedious design handoffs! Turn your Figma designs into working VUE apps in minutes, without writing a single line of code.
Luisa ensures that the design stays the single source of truth.

props.label: Extend the design with business logic by embedding JavaScript to load and store data in backend services. Design changes are seamlessly updates and without overwriting your code.
The unique low-code approach allows to fastly iterate through different design concepts while providing real business functionality to your early users.

Create your design in Figma and use the our Plugin to define which elements will be rendered as real input elements in the browser. As an alternative you can also use Quant-UX to take advantage of a rich palette of fully functional widgets.
Install the luisa-vue package in your VUE project and use the <Luisa> component to render your design on the fly. Design changes as updated instantaneously.
Write custom callback functions and wire them with our Plugin to the right elements. Define a view model and bind it to Figma elements to show dynamic data and read user input.
Once your application is ready, freeze the design deploy the app to your provider of choice. All apps are fully self contained and run as fast as normal Single page applciation build with VUE.

Luisa replaces all front end code, such as *.vue and *css files.  You simply include the <Figma> component which renders your design. Data and your business logic is linked through data and method binding.

Your are still optimizing and changing your design frequently. Normally this would drive your developers nuts, but Luisa takes care of all the conversion from design to code. You decouple your design team from the development team, while Luisa serves as the common interface.

Figma prototypes are awesome, but sometimes you would like to make them more realistic for better demos or user tests. Luisa allows you to embed custom business logic and wire your backend services, so the prototype becomes are real application.
You just want to test your idea in the market and do not want to overspend in development. With Luisa you can cut the front end development time by up to 80% and reduce the time to market and costs.
Below you can find an example for a simple ToDo app. It was design in Figma and wired with some simple backend logic. The app app works, you can enter data, edit, and delete it. Try it out.
